commit.message:
Fix SVG structure for some device graphics

To address warning emitted by Qt:
"Could not add child element to parent element because the types are
incorrect."

Caused by multiple <tspan> attributes inside <text>.

However, by design, the BlackWidow Chroma "M Keys" graphics have
multiple <tspan> to mimic the physical print on the keys. In the distant
future, the program may separate key labels from the SVG for improved
localisation (#373), so not one to worry about.

See also: a1608ed8d04da152d3beec0f9c241b2667173141 (#501)

Use consistent volume icons across device graphics

Emojis removed as they can be inconsistent between other systems,
depending on the fonts installed.

The BlackWidow Elite is an exception as it has a funky lighting layout
around those buttons, but got a bit of a polish.

commit.message:
Troubleshooter: Check older Python site-package directories

For example, this can happen in Arch Linux when the package was
installed and built against Python 3.9, but the system is now running
Python 3.10. AUR/foreign packages need manual intervention.

Not a problem on Debian/Ubuntu, as they install to
"python3/dist-packages".

commit.message:
Realign F1-F8 position for Razer Cynosa V2 (Nordic) graphic

The physical hardware is arranged with the F1 key above the 2. As a
guess, this little detail was missed because it was based on the
BlackWidow Chroma.

Inspired by #500.
